<plot>The street noise of Queens, New York forms a rhythmic backdrop for a Filipina video clerk whose life of quiet isolation is disrupted by an older woman. Rich in location shots redolent of the dislocation of movement even in their ultra-crisp stillness, GREEN STALK reaches for rootedness while admitting its impossibility. Through its "queer eye," the urban United States is disordered, displaced, remade anew.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?222707</url></doc>
